43struct gmbus_pin {
44 const char *name;
45 int reg;
46};
47
48/* Map gmbus pin pairs to names and registers. */
49static const struct gmbus_pin gmbus_pins[] = {
50 [GMBUS_PIN_SSC] = { "ssc", GPIOB },
51 [GMBUS_PIN_VGADDC] = { "vga", GPIOA },
52 [GMBUS_PIN_PANEL] = { "panel", GPIOC },
53 [GMBUS_PIN_DPC] = { "dpc", GPIOD },
54 [GMBUS_PIN_DPB] = { "dpb", GPIOE },
55 [GMBUS_PIN_DPD] = { "dpd", GPIOF },
56};
57
58static const struct gmbus_pin gmbus_pins_bdw[] = {
59 [GMBUS_PIN_VGADDC] = { "vga", GPIOA },
60 [GMBUS_PIN_DPC] = { "dpc", GPIOD },
61 [GMBUS_PIN_DPB] = { "dpb", GPIOE },
62 [GMBUS_PIN_DPD] = { "dpd", GPIOF },
63};
64
65static const struct gmbus_pin gmbus_pins_skl[] = {
66 [GMBUS_PIN_DPC] = { "dpc", GPIOD },
67 [GMBUS_PIN_DPB] = { "dpb", GPIOE },
68 [GMBUS_PIN_DPD] = { "dpd", GPIOF },
69};
70
71static const struct gmbus_pin gmbus_pins_bxt[] = {
72 [GMBUS_PIN_1_BXT] = { "dpb", PCH_GPIOB },
73 [GMBUS_PIN_2_BXT] = { "dpc", PCH_GPIOC },
74 [GMBUS_PIN_3_BXT] = { "misc", PCH_GPIOD },
75};
76
77/* pin is expected to be valid */
78static const struct gmbus_pin *get_gmbus_pin(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
79 unsigned int pin)
80{
81 if (IS_BROXTON(dev_priv))
82 return &gmbus_pins_bxt[pin];
83 else if (IS_SKYLAKE(dev_priv) || IS_KABYLAKE(dev_priv))
84 return &gmbus_pins_skl[pin];
85 else if (IS_BROADWELL(dev_priv))
86 return &gmbus_pins_bdw[pin];
87 else
88 return &gmbus_pins[pin];
89}
90
91bool intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
92 unsigned int pin)
93{
94 unsigned int size;
95
96 if (IS_BROXTON(dev_priv))
97 size = ARRAY_SIZE(gmbus_pins_bxt);
98 else if (IS_SKYLAKE(dev_priv) || IS_KABYLAKE(dev_priv))
99 size = ARRAY_SIZE(gmbus_pins_skl);
100 else if (IS_BROADWELL(dev_priv))
101 size = ARRAY_SIZE(gmbus_pins_bdw);
102 else
103 size = ARRAY_SIZE(gmbus_pins);
104
105 return pin < size && get_gmbus_pin(dev_priv, pin)->reg;
106}

108/* Intel GPIO access functions */
109
110#define I2C_RISEFALL_TIME 10
111
112static inline struct intel_gmbus *
113to_intel_gmbus(struct i2c_adapter *i2c)
114{
115 return container_of(i2c, struct intel_gmbus, adapter);
116}
117
118void
119intel_i2c_reset(struct drm_device *dev)
120{
121 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
122
123 I915_WRITE(GMBUS0, 0);
124 I915_WRITE(GMBUS4, 0);
125}
126
127static void intel_i2c_quirk_set(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, bool enable)
128{
129 u32 val;
130
131 /* When using bit bashing for I2C, this bit needs to be set to 1 */
132 if (!IS_PINEVIEW(dev_priv->dev))
133 return;
134
135 val = I915_READ(DSPCLK_GATE_D);
136 if (enable)
137 val |= DPCUNIT_CLOCK_GATE_DISABLE;
138 else
139 val &= ~DPCUNIT_CLOCK_GATE_DISABLE;
140 I915_WRITE(DSPCLK_GATE_D, val);
141}
142
143static u32 get_reserved(struct intel_gmbus *bus)
144{
145 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
146 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
147 u32 reserved = 0;
148
149 /* On most chips, these bits must be preserved in software. */
150 if (!IS_I830(dev) && !IS_845G(dev))
151 reserved = I915_READ_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg) &
152 (GPIO_DATA_PULLUP_DISABLE |
153 GPIO_CLOCK_PULLUP_DISABLE);
154
155 return reserved;
156}
157
158static int get_clock(void *data)
159{
160 struct intel_gmbus *bus = data;
161 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
162 u32 reserved = get_reserved(bus);
163 I915_WRITE_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg, reserved | GPIO_CLOCK_DIR_MASK);
164 I915_WRITE_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg, reserved);
165 return (I915_READ_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg) & GPIO_CLOCK_VAL_IN) != 0;
166}
167
168static int get_data(void *data)
169{
170 struct intel_gmbus *bus = data;
171 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
172 u32 reserved = get_reserved(bus);
173 I915_WRITE_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg, reserved | GPIO_DATA_DIR_MASK);
174 I915_WRITE_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg, reserved);
175 return (I915_READ_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg) & GPIO_DATA_VAL_IN) != 0;
176}
177
178static void set_clock(void *data, int state_high)
179{
180 struct intel_gmbus *bus = data;
181 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
182 u32 reserved = get_reserved(bus);
183 u32 clock_bits;
184
185 if (state_high)
186 clock_bits = GPIO_CLOCK_DIR_IN | GPIO_CLOCK_DIR_MASK;
187 else
188 clock_bits = GPIO_CLOCK_DIR_OUT | GPIO_CLOCK_DIR_MASK |
189 GPIO_CLOCK_VAL_MASK;
190
191 I915_WRITE_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg, reserved | clock_bits);
192 POSTING_READ(bus->gpio_reg);
193}
194
195static void set_data(void *data, int state_high)
196{
197 struct intel_gmbus *bus = data;
198 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
199 u32 reserved = get_reserved(bus);
200 u32 data_bits;
201
202 if (state_high)
203 data_bits = GPIO_DATA_DIR_IN | GPIO_DATA_DIR_MASK;
204 else
205 data_bits = GPIO_DATA_DIR_OUT | GPIO_DATA_DIR_MASK |
206 GPIO_DATA_VAL_MASK;
207
208 I915_WRITE_NOTRACE(bus->gpio_reg, reserved | data_bits);
209 POSTING_READ(bus->gpio_reg);
210}
211
212static int
213intel_gpio_pre_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
214{
215 struct intel_gmbus *bus = container_of(adapter,
216 struct intel_gmbus,
217 adapter);
218 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
219
220 intel_i2c_reset(dev_priv->dev);
221 intel_i2c_quirk_set(dev_priv, true);
222 set_data(bus, 1);
223 set_clock(bus, 1);
224 udelay(I2C_RISEFALL_TIME);
225 return 0;
226}
227
228static void
229intel_gpio_post_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
230{
231 struct intel_gmbus *bus = container_of(adapter,
232 struct intel_gmbus,
233 adapter);
234 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
235
236 set_data(bus, 1);
237 set_clock(bus, 1);
238 intel_i2c_quirk_set(dev_priv, false);
239}
240
241static void
242intel_gpio_setup(struct intel_gmbus *bus, unsigned int pin)
243{
244 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
245 struct i2c_algo_bit_data *algo;
246
247 algo = &bus->bit_algo;
248
249 bus->gpio_reg = dev_priv->gpio_mmio_base +
250 get_gmbus_pin(dev_priv, pin)->reg;
251
252 bus->adapter.algo_data = algo;
253 algo->setsda = set_data;
254 algo->setscl = set_clock;
255 algo->getsda = get_data;
256 algo->getscl = get_clock;
257 algo->pre_xfer = intel_gpio_pre_xfer;
258 algo->post_xfer = intel_gpio_post_xfer;
259 algo->udelay = I2C_RISEFALL_TIME;
260 algo->timeout = usecs_to_jiffies(2200);
261 algo->data = bus;
262}
263
264static int
265gmbus_wait_hw_status(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
266 u32 gmbus2_status,
267 u32 gmbus4_irq_en)
268{
269 int i;
270 u32 gmbus2 = 0;
271#ifndef __NetBSD__
272 DEFINE_WAIT(wait);
273#endif
274
275#ifdef __NetBSD__
276 if (cold || !HAS_GMBUS_IRQ(dev_priv->dev))
277 gmbus4_irq_en = 0;
278#else
279 if (!HAS_GMBUS_IRQ(dev_priv->dev))
280 gmbus4_irq_en = 0;
281#endif
282
283 /* Important: The hw handles only the first bit, so set only one! Since
284 * we also need to check for NAKs besides the hw ready/idle signal, we
285 * need to wake up periodically and check that ourselves. */
286 I915_WRITE(GMBUS4, gmbus4_irq_en);
287
288#ifdef __NetBSD__
289 if (cold) {
290 i = 50;
291 do {
292 gmbus2 = I915_READ_NOTRACE(GMBUS2);
293 if (ISSET(gmbus2, (GMBUS_SATOER | gmbus2_status)))
294 break;
295 DELAY(1000);
296 } while (i-- > 0);
297 } else {
298 i = mstohz(50);
299 do {
300 int ret;
301
302 spin_lock(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
303 DRM_SPIN_TIMED_WAIT_NOINTR_UNTIL(ret,
304 &dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue,
305 &dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock,
306 1,
307 (gmbus2 = I915_READ_NOTRACE(GMBUS2),
308 ISSET(gmbus2,
309 (GMBUS_SATOER | gmbus2_status))));
310 spin_unlock(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
311 if (ret)
312 break;
313 } while (i-- > 0);
314 }
315#else
316 for (i = 0; i < msecs_to_jiffies_timeout(50); i++) {
317 prepare_to_wait(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue, &wait,
318 TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE);
319
320 gmbus2 = I915_READ_NOTRACE(GMBUS2);
321 if (gmbus2 & (GMBUS_SATOER | gmbus2_status))
322 break;
323
324 schedule_timeout(1);
325 }
326 finish_wait(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue, &wait);
327#endif
328
329 I915_WRITE(GMBUS4, 0);
330
331 if (gmbus2 & GMBUS_SATOER)
332 return -ENXIO;
333 if (gmbus2 & gmbus2_status)
334 return 0;
335 return -ETIMEDOUT;
336}
337
338static int
339gmbus_wait_idle(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv)
340{
341 int ret;
342
343#define C ((I915_READ_NOTRACE(GMBUS2) & GMBUS_ACTIVE) == 0)
344
345#ifdef __NetBSD__
346 if (cold || !HAS_GMBUS_IRQ(dev_priv->dev))
347 return wait_for(C, 10);
348#else
349 if (!HAS_GMBUS_IRQ(dev_priv->dev))
350 return wait_for(C, 10);
351#endif
352
353 /* Important: The hw handles only the first bit, so set only one! */
354 I915_WRITE(GMBUS4, GMBUS_IDLE_EN);
355
356#ifdef __NetBSD__
357 spin_lock(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
358 DRM_SPIN_TIMED_WAIT_NOINTR_UNTIL(ret, &dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue,
359 &dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock, msecs_to_jiffies_timeout(10),
360 C);
361 spin_unlock(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
362#else
363 ret = wait_event_timeout(dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue, C,
364 msecs_to_jiffies_timeout(10));
365#endif
366
367 I915_WRITE(GMBUS4, 0);
368
369 if (ret)
370 return 0;
371 else
372 return -ETIMEDOUT;
373#undef C
374}
375
376static int
377gmbus_xfer_read_chunk(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
378 unsigned short addr, u8 *buf, unsigned int len,
379 u32 gmbus1_index)
380{
381 I915_WRITE(GMBUS1,
382 gmbus1_index |
383 GMBUS_CYCLE_WAIT |
384 (len << GMBUS_BYTE_COUNT_SHIFT) |
385 (addr << GMBUS_SLAVE_ADDR_SHIFT) |
386 GMBUS_SLAVE_READ | GMBUS_SW_RDY);
387 while (len) {
388 int ret;
389 u32 val, loop = 0;
390
391 ret = gmbus_wait_hw_status(dev_priv, GMBUS_HW_RDY,
392 GMBUS_HW_RDY_EN);
393 if (ret)
394 return ret;
395
396 val = I915_READ(GMBUS3);
397 do {
398 *buf++ = val & 0xff;
399 val >>= 8;
400 } while (--len && ++loop < 4);
401 }
402
403 return 0;
404}
405
406static int
407gmbus_xfer_read(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, struct i2c_msg *msg,
408 u32 gmbus1_index)
409{
410 u8 *buf = msg->buf;
411 unsigned int rx_size = msg->len;
412 unsigned int len;
413 int ret;
414
415 do {
416 len = min(rx_size, GMBUS_BYTE_COUNT_MAX);
417
418 ret = gmbus_xfer_read_chunk(dev_priv, msg->addr,
419 buf, len, gmbus1_index);
420 if (ret)
421 return ret;
422
423 rx_size -= len;
424 buf += len;
425 } while (rx_size != 0);
426
427 return 0;
428}
429
430static int
431gmbus_xfer_write_chunk(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
432 unsigned short addr, u8 *buf, unsigned int len)
433{
434 unsigned int chunk_size = len;
435 u32 val, loop;
436
437 val = loop = 0;
438 while (len && loop < 4) {
439 val |= *buf++ << (8 * loop++);
440 len -= 1;
441 }
442
443 I915_WRITE(GMBUS3, val);
444 I915_WRITE(GMBUS1,
445 GMBUS_CYCLE_WAIT |
446 (chunk_size << GMBUS_BYTE_COUNT_SHIFT) |
447 (addr << GMBUS_SLAVE_ADDR_SHIFT) |
448 GMBUS_SLAVE_WRITE | GMBUS_SW_RDY);
449 while (len) {
450 int ret;
451
452 val = loop = 0;
453 do {
454 val |= *buf++ << (8 * loop);
455 } while (--len && ++loop < 4);
456
457 I915_WRITE(GMBUS3, val);
458
459 ret = gmbus_wait_hw_status(dev_priv, GMBUS_HW_RDY,
460 GMBUS_HW_RDY_EN);
461 if (ret)
462 return ret;
463 }
464
465 return 0;
466}
467
468static int
469gmbus_xfer_write(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, struct i2c_msg *msg)
470{
471 u8 *buf = msg->buf;
472 unsigned int tx_size = msg->len;
473 unsigned int len;
474 int ret;
475
476 do {
477 len = min(tx_size, GMBUS_BYTE_COUNT_MAX);
478
479 ret = gmbus_xfer_write_chunk(dev_priv, msg->addr, buf, len);
480 if (ret)
481 return ret;
482
483 buf += len;
484 tx_size -= len;
485 } while (tx_size != 0);
486
487 return 0;
488}
489
490/*
491 * The gmbus controller can combine a 1 or 2 byte write with a read that
492 * immediately follows it by using an "INDEX" cycle.
493 */
494static bool
495gmbus_is_index_read(struct i2c_msg *msgs, int i, int num)
496{
497 return (i + 1 < num &&
498 msgs[i].addr == msgs[i + 1].addr &&
499 !(msgs[i].flags & I2C_M_RD) &&
500 (msgs[i].len == 1 || msgs[i].len == 2) &&
501 (msgs[i + 1].flags & I2C_M_RD));
502}
503
504static int
505gmbus_xfer_index_read(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, struct i2c_msg *msgs)
506{
507 u32 gmbus1_index = 0;
508 u32 gmbus5 = 0;
509 int ret;
510
511 if (msgs[0].len == 2)
512 gmbus5 = GMBUS_2BYTE_INDEX_EN |
513 msgs[0].buf[1] | (msgs[0].buf[0] << 8);
514 if (msgs[0].len == 1)
515 gmbus1_index = GMBUS_CYCLE_INDEX |
516 (msgs[0].buf[0] << GMBUS_SLAVE_INDEX_SHIFT);
517
518 /* GMBUS5 holds 16-bit index */
519 if (gmbus5)
520 I915_WRITE(GMBUS5, gmbus5);
521
522 ret = gmbus_xfer_read(dev_priv, &msgs[1], gmbus1_index);
523
524 /* Clear GMBUS5 after each index transfer */
525 if (gmbus5)
526 I915_WRITE(GMBUS5, 0);
527
528 return ret;
529}
530
531static int
532gmbus_xfer(struct i2c_adapter *adapter,
533 struct i2c_msg *msgs,
534 int num)
535{
536 struct intel_gmbus *bus = container_of(adapter,
537 struct intel_gmbus,
538 adapter);
539 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = bus->dev_priv;
540 int i = 0, inc, try = 0;
541 int ret = 0;
542
543 intel_display_power_get(dev_priv, POWER_DOMAIN_GMBUS);
544 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->gmbus_mutex);
545
546 if (bus->force_bit) {
547 ret = i2c_bit_algo.master_xfer(adapter, msgs, num);
548 goto out;
549 }
550
551retry:
552 I915_WRITE(GMBUS0, bus->reg0);
553
554 for (; i < num; i += inc) {
555 inc = 1;
556 if (gmbus_is_index_read(msgs, i, num)) {
557 ret = gmbus_xfer_index_read(dev_priv, &msgs[i]);
558 inc = 2; /* an index read is two msgs */
559 } else if (msgs[i].flags & I2C_M_RD) {
560 ret = gmbus_xfer_read(dev_priv, &msgs[i], 0);
561 } else {
562 ret = gmbus_xfer_write(dev_priv, &msgs[i]);
563 }
564
565 if (ret == -ETIMEDOUT)
566 goto timeout;
567 if (ret == -ENXIO)
568 goto clear_err;
569
570 ret = gmbus_wait_hw_status(dev_priv, GMBUS_HW_WAIT_PHASE,
571 GMBUS_HW_WAIT_EN);
572 if (ret == -ENXIO)
573 goto clear_err;
574 if (ret)
575 goto timeout;
576 }
577
578 /* Generate a STOP condition on the bus. Note that gmbus can't generata
579 * a STOP on the very first cycle. To simplify the code we
580 * unconditionally generate the STOP condition with an additional gmbus
581 * cycle. */
582 I915_WRITE(GMBUS1, GMBUS_CYCLE_STOP | GMBUS_SW_RDY);
583
584 /* Mark the GMBUS interface as disabled after waiting for idle.
585 * We will re-enable it at the start of the next xfer,
586 * till then let it sleep.
587 */
588 if (gmbus_wait_idle(dev_priv)) {
589 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("GMBUS [%s] timed out waiting for idle\n",
590 adapter->name);
591 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
592 }
593 I915_WRITE(GMBUS0, 0);
594 ret = ret ?: i;
595 goto out;
596
597clear_err:
598 /*
599 * Wait for bus to IDLE before clearing NAK.
600 * If we clear the NAK while bus is still active, then it will stay
601 * active and the next transaction may fail.
602 *
603 * If no ACK is received during the address phase of a transaction, the
604 * adapter must report -ENXIO. It is not clear what to return if no ACK
605 * is received at other times. But we have to be careful to not return
606 * spurious -ENXIO because that will prevent i2c and drm edid functions
607 * from retrying. So return -ENXIO only when gmbus properly quiescents -
608 * timing out seems to happen when there _is_ a ddc chip present, but
609 * it's slow responding and only answers on the 2nd retry.
610 */
611 ret = -ENXIO;
612 if (gmbus_wait_idle(dev_priv)) {
613 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("GMBUS [%s] timed out after NAK\n",
614 adapter->name);
615 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
616 }
617
618 /* Toggle the Software Clear Interrupt bit. This has the effect
619 * of resetting the GMBUS controller and so clearing the
620 * BUS_ERROR raised by the slave's NAK.
621 */
622 I915_WRITE(GMBUS1, GMBUS_SW_CLR_INT);
623 I915_WRITE(GMBUS1, 0);
624 I915_WRITE(GMBUS0, 0);
625
626 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("GMBUS [%s] NAK for addr: %04x %c(%d)\n",
627 adapter->name, msgs[i].addr,
628 (msgs[i].flags & I2C_M_RD) ? 'r' : 'w', msgs[i].len);
629
630 /*
631 * Passive adapters sometimes NAK the first probe. Retry the first
632 * message once on -ENXIO for GMBUS transfers; the bit banging algorithm
633 * has retries internally. See also the retry loop in
634 * drm_do_probe_ddc_edid, which bails out on the first -ENXIO.
635 */
636 if (ret == -ENXIO && i == 0 && try++ == 0) {
637 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("GMBUS [%s] NAK on first message, retry\n",
638 adapter->name);
639 goto retry;
640 }
641
642 goto out;
643
644timeout:
645 DRM_INFO("GMBUS [%s] timed out, falling back to bit banging on pin %d\n",
646 bus->adapter.name, bus->reg0 & 0xff);
647 I915_WRITE(GMBUS0, 0);
648
649 /* Hardware may not support GMBUS over these pins? Try GPIO bitbanging instead. */
650 bus->force_bit = 1;
651 ret = i2c_bit_algo.master_xfer(adapter, msgs, num);
652
653out:
654 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->gmbus_mutex);
655
656 intel_display_power_put(dev_priv, POWER_DOMAIN_GMBUS);
657
658 return ret;
659}
660
661static u32 gmbus_func(struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
662{
663 return i2c_bit_algo.functionality(adapter) &
664 (I2C_FUNC_I2C | I2C_FUNC_SMBUS_EMUL |
665 /* I2C_FUNC_10BIT_ADDR | */
666 I2C_FUNC_SMBUS_READ_BLOCK_DATA |
667 I2C_FUNC_SMBUS_BLOCK_PROC_CALL);
668}
669
670static const struct i2c_algorithm gmbus_algorithm = {
671 .master_xfer = gmbus_xfer,
672 .functionality = gmbus_func
673};
674
675/**
676 * intel_gmbus_setup - instantiate all Intel i2c GMBuses
677 * @dev: DRM device
678 */
679int intel_setup_gmbus(struct drm_device *dev)
680{
681 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
682 struct intel_gmbus *bus;
683 unsigned int pin;
684 int ret;
685
686 if (HAS_PCH_NOP(dev))
687 return 0;
688 else if (HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev))
689 dev_priv->gpio_mmio_base = PCH_GPIOA - GPIOA;
690 else if (IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev))
691 dev_priv->gpio_mmio_base = VLV_DISPLAY_BASE;
692 else
693 dev_priv->gpio_mmio_base = 0;
694
695#ifdef __NetBSD__
696 linux_mutex_init(&dev_priv->gmbus_mutex);
697#else
698 mutex_init(&dev_priv->gmbus_mutex);
699#endif
700
701#ifdef __NetBSD__
702 spin_lock_init(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
703 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue, "i915i2c");
704#else
705 init_waitqueue_head(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue);
706#endif
707
708 for (pin = 0; pin < ARRAY_SIZE(dev_priv->gmbus); pin++) {
709 if (!intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, pin))
710 continue;
711
712 bus = &dev_priv->gmbus[pin];
713
714 bus->adapter.owner = THIS_MODULE;
715 bus->adapter.class = I2C_CLASS_DDC;
716 snprintf(bus->adapter.name,
717 sizeof(bus->adapter.name),
718 "i915 gmbus %s",
719 get_gmbus_pin(dev_priv, pin)->name);
720
721#ifdef __NetBSD__
722 bus->adapter.dev.parent = dev->dev;
723#else
724 bus->adapter.dev.parent = &dev->pdev->dev;
725#endif
726 bus->dev_priv = dev_priv;
727
728 bus->adapter.algo = &gmbus_algorithm;
729
730 /* By default use a conservative clock rate */
731 bus->reg0 = pin | GMBUS_RATE_100KHZ;
732
733 /* gmbus seems to be broken on i830 */
734 if (IS_I830(dev))
735 bus->force_bit = 1;
736
737 intel_gpio_setup(bus, pin);
738
739 ret = i2c_add_adapter(&bus->adapter);
740 if (ret)
741 goto err;
742 }
743
744 intel_i2c_reset(dev_priv->dev);
745
746 return 0;
747
748err:
749 while (pin--) {
750 if (!intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, pin))
751 continue;
752
753 bus = &dev_priv->gmbus[pin];
754 i2c_del_adapter(&bus->adapter);
755 }
756 return ret;
757}
758
759struct i2c_adapter *intel_gmbus_get_adapter(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
760 unsigned int pin)
761{
762 if (WARN_ON(!intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, pin)))
763 return NULL;
764
765 return &dev_priv->gmbus[pin].adapter;
766}
767
768void intel_gmbus_set_speed(struct i2c_adapter *adapter, int speed)
769{
770 struct intel_gmbus *bus = to_intel_gmbus(adapter);
771
772 bus->reg0 = (bus->reg0 & ~(0x3 << 8)) | speed;
773}
774
775void intel_gmbus_force_bit(struct i2c_adapter *adapter, bool force_bit)
776{
777 struct intel_gmbus *bus = to_intel_gmbus(adapter);
778
779 bus->force_bit += force_bit ? 1 : -1;
780 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%sabling bit-banging on %s. force bit now %d\n",
781 force_bit ? "en" : "dis", adapter->name,
782 bus->force_bit);
783}
784
785void intel_teardown_gmbus(struct drm_device *dev)
786{
787 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
788 struct intel_gmbus *bus;
789 unsigned int pin;
790
791 for (pin = 0; pin < ARRAY_SIZE(dev_priv->gmbus); pin++) {
792 if (!intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, pin))
793 continue;
794
795 bus = &dev_priv->gmbus[pin];
796 i2c_del_adapter(&bus->adapter);
797 }
798
799#ifdef __NetBSD__
800 DRM_DESTROY_WAITQUEUE(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_queue);
801 spin_lock_destroy(&dev_priv->gmbus_wait_lock);
802 linux_mutex_destroy(&dev_priv->gmbus_mutex);
803#endif
804}
